races.description: The Half-Dragons have been a space faring race for quite a long time, contrary to popular belief these noble yet somewhat savage folk are not genetically engineered. They are easily spotted by their physical differences with humans thanks to their colorful scales, draconic eyes, horns and even tails! Thanks to their physical differences and strong scales people of this race proved themselves to be excellent melee combatants. It was easy to find them serving various empires outside of their own as front line fighters. Sadly due to their hardy nature and exotic looks many Half-Dragons end up captured and forced into gladiatorial combat. There are other reasons they are highly sought after; unique biological traits that are wholly unique to them. One of which allows to combine a specialized ore with their blood that activates various powerful abilities. A point of debate of many scholars is how such a openly savage race had made it to spaceflight, much less a force that roams about the galaxy. This is in large part thanks to a rare sub group of Half-Dragons that lead their kind in political, cultural and scientific endeavors. These "albino's" are almost the polar opposites of their more common brutish brethren. Despite a strong imperial nation and a sense of loyalty to their own, those that find themselves able to escape their gladiatorial slavery often form up as pirates. These pirates tend to be ruthless and a general nuisance in the galaxy. Half dragons (Half dragons)

They are created by channeling the untapped psychic energies of the collective unconscious to acheive unparaleled firepower miniaturization, at a cost of giving them somewhat eclectic personalities and appearances. Be aware that loading them down with heavy cannons and armor with lower their movement ability and amplify their prodigious appetites. They often resemble tribal deities, colorful pop stars, or historical figures whose names they bear. Ship Girl Race (Ship Girl Race)
races.name: Ship Girl

races.description: The legacy of a fallen empire, with a distant link to the humanoid races of earth and beyond. Other than the fact that they began to awaken over the past century, no one knows much else about what they are, where they are from or fundamentals behind their technology, which seems to bridge the gap between science and magic. Forsakens (Forsakens)
races.name: forsaken

races.description: The geth are a race of networked artificial intelligences that reside beyond the Perseus Veil. The geth were created by the quarians as laborers and tools of war. When the geth became sentient and began to question their masters, the quarians attempted to exterminate them. Mass Effect - Playable Geth (Mass Effect - Playable Geth)
races.name: Geth

races.description: The geth are a race of networked artificial intelligences that reside beyond the Perseus Veil. The geth were created by the quarians as laborers and tools of war. When the geth became sentient and began to question their masters, the quarians attempted to exterminate them. Mass Effect - Playable Geth (Mass Effect - Playable Geth)
races.name: Geth Prime

races.description: The geth are a race of networked artificial intelligences that reside beyond the Perseus Veil. The geth were created by the quarians as laborers and tools of war. When the geth became sentient and began to question their masters, the quarians attempted to exterminate them. Mass Effect - Playable Geth (Mass Effect - Playable Geth)
races.name: Geth Colossus

races.description: A form of mechanized infantry, produced during an ancient time on this rimworld. These units are very strong, powerful war machines but are subsequently slow and have limited battery to them. Android tiers (Android tiers)
races.name: M7 Mechanised infantry

races.description: A prototype M7 mechanized infantry, equipped with a limited SkyCore unit and SkyMind radio. These units are very strong, powerful war machines and allow digital consciousness to move on battlefields but are subsequently slow and have limited internal storage capacity to them. Android tiers (Android tiers)
races.name: M8 Mechanised infantry

races.description: A lost android, shunned from their transcendant community. The tech used to make them is beyond human comprehension, boasting near unlimited power and requiring little sustinence to operate. They deem all races other than themselves to be somewhat below them and believe that living on a rimworld is a fate worse than death. Android tiers (Android tiers)
races.name: T5 Android

races.description: The most advanced form of android conceivable; this tier is able to efficiently hold the consciousness of any AI uploaded onto it, with advanced locomotive abilities and manipulation; this android vastly suprasses most humans. Android tiers (Android tiers)
races.name: T4 Android

races.description: A Prototype android exclusive to this rimworld; developed by a secret R/D Laboratory, away from the eye of the rest of the planet and cosmos. This android features highly advanced locomotive and motor abilities, perfectly mimicing that of an average human. Although clunky and somewhat slow - this android features a modular component design, allowing for upgrades to be made to current parts at any point. Android tiers (Android tiers)
races.name: T3 Android

races.description: As simple as sentient robotics can get. This design is the bare skeletal amount of components needed to create full autonomous functionality. Obviously not the best but it works well when needed. Android tiers (Android tiers)
races.name: T1 Android

races.description: A somewhat advanced android, capable of almost perfectly storing an AI consciousness and with reasonable levels of motor skills. A good all round android that is uses extensively on glitterworlds for basic maintenance and cleaning. Android tiers (Android tiers)
races.name: T2 Android

races.description: A reclusive and diminishing race of proto-mechanical persona, 'skeletons' are fully sentient and feeling mechanical entities; they were built thousands of years ago as stand-ins for humans during lengthy processes, such as space flight. Since being manufactured they have been replaced by the far more complex mechanoid and AI persona. They have no fear of prejudice or fear of death - and are usually levelheaded thinkers. Being mechanical in nature - 'skeletons' do not need sustenance or rest, but this does not make them invulnerable to "pain" signals, chemical signals, or psychic engines. Furthermore, due to their incredibly long lifespan and common crushing existential dread; most 'skeletons' are depressed or dreadfully pessimistic of their future. Rim-Skeletons (Rim-Skeletons)
races.name: skeleton

races.description: A robotic maid with a simple AI, for all your housekeeping needs! Robot Maid (Robot Maid)
races.name: RobotMaid

races.description: The krogan are a species of large reptilian bipeds native to the planet Tuchanka, a world known for its harsh environments, scarce resources, and overabundance of vicious predators. Bob's Mass Effect Krogans (Bob's Mass Effect Krogans)
races.name: Krogan

races.description: The most distinguishing feature of turians is their metallic carapace. The turians evolved this trait as a defense against the greater levels of solar radiation that penetrate their homeworld's weak magnetic field. Bob's Mass Effect Turians (Bob's Mass Effect Turians)
races.name: Turian

data.mod: RimEffect - Asari of the Rims Continued [1.1+]

races.description: A mono-gender race, the asari are distinctly feminine in appearance and possess maternal instincts. Their unique physiology, expressed in a millennium-long lifespan and the ability to reproduce with a partner of any gender or species, gives them a conservative yet convivial attitude toward other races. RimEffect - Asari of the Rims Continued (1.1+) (RimEffect - Asari of the Rims Continued (1.1+))
races.name: asari

races.description: Inhabitants of lunar cities that carry the genes of rabbits, the rabbie excel at waging war and constructing mega-cities. They travel the galaxy in search of celestial bodies with planetarium; a drug that the rabbie population has been reliant on for survival since the begining of their history. It is believed they originally came from another galaxy, but have sinced lost the technology and have been cut off from their home galaxy. Rabbie The Moonrabbit race (Rabbie The Moonrabbit race)
races.name: Rabbie

races.description: A Xenohuman hailing from a luxurious Glitterworld, genetically modified to enhance charisma, intellect, and to satisfy an odd, bygone fashion trend. This particular Glitterworlder seems to be encrusted in decorative 'gemstones', though the stones are little more than polished calcium deposits grown naturally by their body. Xenohumans Expanded (Xenohumans Expanded)
races.name: glitterworld human

races.description: A Xenohuman whose biology seems to have stemmed from evolutionary adaptations to high-gravity planets. They are quite short, but their strength is unmatched by most. However, their intellectual prowess, or rather lack thereof, is less than impressive. Xenohumans Expanded (Xenohumans Expanded)
races.name: gravity dwarf

races.description: A Xenohuman originating from a planet with significantly lower gravity than usual. Over time, their metabolic resources seem to have redistributed more towards brain development than managing atrophy. As such, they are physically frail but superior to most others intellectually. Xenohumans Expanded (Xenohumans Expanded)
races.name: lo-grav human

races.description: A Xenohuman descendant from surviving denizens of a toxic Radworld. Their immune system has adapted over time to foreign chemical and radiological hazards, making them nigh-immune to diseases and infections. Appearance, it seems, was left by the wayside, and they are quite hideous to look at, much less speak to. Xenohumans Expanded (Xenohumans Expanded)
races.name: radworld human

races.description: A Xenohuman genetically engineered both physically and neurologically to be the perfect worker at a very specific task. Bred and modified for complete and utter obedience at the whims of a now-unknown faction, they excel at most forms of skilled and simple labor, but learn new concepts quite slowly. Xenohumans Expanded (Xenohumans Expanded)
races.name: vatdrone

races.description: Immune to disease. Lives to be 100 years old. Loves to eat, drink, be merry, and sometimes, just sometimes, go on adventures. Lord of the Rims - Hobbits (Lord of the Rims - Hobbits)
races.name: hobbit

races.description: Immune to disease. Lives for 250 years. Loves to mine, craft, and make friends. Lord of the Rims - Dwarves (Lord of the Rims - Dwarves)
races.name: dwarf

races.description: Immune to disease. Wise and immortal. Lord of the Rims - Elves (Lord of the Rims - Elves)
races.name: elf

races.description: Those born between the world of immortality and mortality. Lord of the Rims - Elves (Lord of the Rims - Elves)
races.name: half-elf

races.description: A very uncommon Beastmen. Capable of casting spells, and performing dark rituals. Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen (Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen)
races.name: bray shaman

races.description: Minotaurs, also known as Bullgors, are a massive bull-headed breed of the Beastmen race. Having a large body restricts their use of certain apparel. Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen (Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen)
races.name: bullgor

races.description: The Cygors are distant cousins of the Minotaurs, but because they hail from the most tainted of all the realms of the Old World, they have diverged greatly from their kin. They are huge, hideously malformed giants, similar in form to Minotaurs, yet each possessed of but a single eye that barely can perceive the mortal world. Cursed with a vision that can only see the winds of magic, Cygors are all quite mad, constantly hunted by ghostly shapes that populate their world. Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen (Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen)
races.name: cygor

races.description: A gor that has been gifted by the Lord Khorne. They're better fighters than regular gor, and are revered amongst their kin for their skills and savagery in battle. Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen (Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen)
races.name: khornegor

races.description: A gor that has been blessed by Papa Nurgle. They're better fighters than regular gor, tend to recover from injuries and disease faster than most. Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen (Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen)
races.name: pestigor

races.description: A gor that has received the charms of Slaanesh. They're better fighters than regular gor, and are revered amongst their kin for their speed and skill. Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen (Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen)
races.name: slaangor

races.description: A gor that has received the power and blessing of Tzeentch. They're better fighters than regular gor, and are revered amongst their kin for their magical potential and skills. Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen (Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen)
races.name: tzaangor

races.description: A common breed of the Beastmen. They make up the bulk of the beastmen herds roaming the lands. Gors tend to be vicious and bloodthirsty, but the rarer beastwomen tends to have a gentler side. Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen (Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen)
races.name: gor

races.description: A lower breed of beastmen. They are either born as mutants or changed into ones later in their lifes. Outcasts from human society they turn to the gor herds as a lower cast. Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen (Rimhammer - The End Times - Beastmen)
races.name: ungor

races.description: Whether due to scientific experimentation, occult interference, or comic fluke, these are poor souls for whom death has been abjured. Call of Cthulhu - Cults (Call of Cthulhu - Cults)
races.name: reanimated corpse

races.description: The Blood Elves or Sin'dorei in Thalassian ("children of the blood"), are a race composed of former high elves who renamed themselves in honor of their people who were killed during the siege of Quel'Thalas by the Scourge during the Third War. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: blood elf

races.description: The draenei (meaning Exiled Ones in their own tongue) are a faction of uncorrupted eredar who fled their homeworld of Argus to escape the corruption of the demonic Burning Legion. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: Draenei

races.description: Dwarves are an ancient bold and courageous race descended from the earthen. Dwarves are short and stout creatures. They are shorter than humans but taller than gnomes, taking advantage of their size when possible and relying on their robustness and strength when not. The average dwarf is steady, observant and composed both during work and combat, yet able to rage with fierce zeal and persistence when the situation calls for it. While a dwarf prefers to plan forward to overcome challenges, many of them easily lose their temperament and self-restraint when exposed to conditions stirring their feelings and concerns. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: Dwarf

races.description: The undead Forsaken or simply the Forsaken and Undead are a race and a faction of intelligent undead who broke away from the Scourge and took control of much of the kingdom of Lordaeron, destroyed during the Third War by the death knight Arthas. While comprised vastly of undead humans, the Forsaken are a diverse faction that include several different races at their biological core. However, they have all assumed their racial identity as "Forsaken," due to their shared goals and loyalties. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: forsaken

races.description: The Night Elves are a powerful and mystical race whose origins extend back to ancient times. These then-immortal beings were among the first to study magic and let it loose throughout the world nearly ten thousand years before the First War on Azeroth. The far-reaching and ancient legacy of the night elves shaped them into a race of very self-sufficient and self-conscious individuals, who often display strong streaks of isolationism. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: Forsaken Night Elf

races.description: The Blood Elves or Sin'dorei in Thalassian ("children of the blood"), are a race composed of former high elves who renamed themselves in honor of their people who were killed during the siege of Quel'Thalas by the Scourge during the Third War. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: Forsaken High Elf

races.description: The gnomes (collectively referred to as gnomanity or gnomekind) are a race of diminutive and highly intelligent humanoids, known for their mastery of technology. They were originally descended from mechagnomes, metallic titan-forged, who were afflicted with the Curse of Flesh. Gnomes are a race of ambitious folk that celebrate creativity and craft and whose lives are validated by a masterful command of the scientific laws of the universe. This outlook on life makes them feel that to be pitied is unbearable, even insulting, though they know their allies do not do this intentionally. They have been more of a race of scholars throughout their history, generally focused on escaping and avoiding conflict, being also known to offset their lack of physical strength with ingenuity and daring. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: Gnome

races.description: The goblins (collectively known as goblinhood) are small green humanoids from the Isle of Kezan. Their love of money, explosives, and technology leaves them to be a very dangerous race, both to their enemies and themselves. Most goblins have a neutral standpoint, preferring to sell their contraptions, knowledge and services to other races. Goblins are slight and wiry, averaging 4 feet in height.[21][22][23] They have three fingers and one thumb on one hand and four toes on one foot. Their noses grow larger as they age. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: Goblin

races.description: The High Elves, or Quel'dorei ("children of noble birth"), are a race descended from the Highborne night elves who left Kalimdor and settled in the Eastern Kingdoms, founding Quel'Thalas. The high elves were once a significant force on the continent, but in recent times their numbers have been dramatically reduced: almost 90% of their population in Quel'Thalas was slaughtered during the Third War. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: high elf

races.description: Humans (collectively referred to as mankind or humanity) are a resilient species native to the world of Azeroth. Recent discoveries have shown that humans are descended from the barbaric half-giant vrykul of Northrend. Though humans are among the younger races on Azeroth, they have faced many challenges with fortitude and resilience. Their continued ability to adapt and rebuild has made them a vital force in an ever-changing world. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: azerothian human

races.description: The Night Elves are a powerful and mystical race whose origins extend back to ancient times. These then-immortal beings were among the first to study magic and let it loose throughout the world nearly ten thousand years before the First War on Azeroth. The far-reaching and ancient legacy of the night elves shaped them into a race of very self-sufficient and self-conscious individuals, who often display strong streaks of isolationism. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: night elf

races.description: The orcs are a race native to the world of Draenor, now known as Outland, they arrived to Azeroth through the Dark Portal a massive structure that allowed orcs passage from their world. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: Orc

races.description: The tauren (shu'halo in their native language of Taur-ahe) are a race of large, bovine humanoids who dwell on the great plains of Central Kalimdor. For countless generations, they were constantly harassed by the violent centaur, who forced the tauren into a nomadic lifestyle in the harsh Barrens. Despite their enormous size, the tauren are a peaceful and honorable people who nonetheless are fierce fighters when roused. Hunting and shamanism are held in high regard in their culture, as is their worship of the Earth Mother and respect for the land and nature. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: Tauren

races.description: Trolls (collectively referred to as trollkind) are a diverse sapient race that can be found in every part of Azeroth. They are one of the earliest known native races of Azeroth. Trolls are a species where multiple subspecies exist, these subspecies vary from being tall, lanky and muscular, with each subspecies being different than the others both physically and culturally. They have both elven and orc-like characteristics with their fierce tusks and long ears. Their long arms, strong legs, quick reflexes as well as their incredible agility and strength make them adept hunters. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: Troll

races.description: The worgen are a race of feral wolf-beasts whose very name inspires fear. They are large, lupine humanoids that walk upright, but lope on all fours to run. Being bitten by or drinking the blood of a worgen causes humans and night elves to be transformed into one. After the transformation, those that are overcome by rage and guilt gradually lose all vestiges of their former lives and turn mindless. By controlling their emotions via medication, magic, and self-discipline, worgen may resist being overcome by their feral instincts. (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: Worgen

races.description: Skeleton of the Scourge (Ry)Rimcraft ((Ry)Rimcraft)
races.name: skeleton

races.description: A warhammer themed dwarf. Relatively immune to disease due to high constitution. Live for 400 years or so typically, but can be as old as 700 years. Love gold, as well as to mine, build, and craft. Collectively known as dawi in their own language: khazalid. Rimhammer - The End Times - Dwarfs (Rimhammer - The End Times - Dwarfs)
races.name: dwarf

races.description: Relatively immune to disease due to high constitution. Live for 400 years or so typically, but can be as old as 700 years. Love gold, as well as to mine, build, and craft. Slayers are warriors, they've suffered such a great dishonor that they have decided to seek death at the hands of the biggest, most fearsome enemy they can find. Rimhammer - The End Times - Dwarfs (Rimhammer - The End Times - Dwarfs)
races.name: slayer

races.description: Void elves (or ren'dorei, "children of the Void" in Thalassian) are a race of Void-infused elves affiliated with the Alliance. Their origins lie with a group of blood elves led by Magister Umbric who were exiled from Silvermoon City because of their research into the Void. They were transformed by void ethereals but rescued by Alleria Windrunner, who had gained mastery of the Void herself on Argus. Permanently transformed by the process, they pledged their loyalty to her and the Alliance and established themselves as the ren'dorei. The void elves seek to utilize their great but dangerous powers for the sake of defending Azeroth and the Alliance, and to prove those who doubt or judge their abilities wrong, all the while resisting the Void's call to madness. (Ry)Rimcraft Allied Races ((Ry)Rimcraft Allied Races)
races.name: void elf

races.description: The Mag'har orcs ("uncorrupted" in Orcish), also known as "brown orcs", are the orcs that escaped the corruption of the Burning Legion. On Draenor, they were a result of isolation from the Horde due to being quarantined in Garadar. They have a noble shamanistic tradition cultivating a mighty tribal society that was centered around survival, regulating themselves through ritualized combat and personal honor. (Ry)Rimcraft Allied Races ((Ry)Rimcraft Allied Races)
races.name: Mag'har Orc

races.description: The Nightborne or Shal'dorei in the native tongue, are a powerful and mystical race of elves who live in Suramar. Since the city was first separated from the rest of the world over 10,000 years ago, they are no longer true night elves and have evolved by the Nightwell into a unique elven species. For the majority of their secluded existence, virtually the entire group resided in the ancient city of Suramar and were led solely until recent times by Grand Magistrix Elisande. The nightborne race owes much of its unique physical characteristics to its long dependence on the Nightwell, an ancient source of power crafted by Suramar's Highborne residents during the War of the Ancients. Over their lengthy isolation, the exposure of the nightborne to the Nightwell's energies gradually transformed them from their original Kaldorei night elven appearance to their present darker, more night-based form. (Ry)Rimcraft Allied Races ((Ry)Rimcraft Allied Races)
races.name: nightborne

races.name: Zombie
